canonical:
  title: 次聞慶縣主屹靈祠韻
  author: 權擥
  language: lzh
  text: 祕殿靑山下陰機白日中人情聊報祀神意肯邀功
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 次聞慶縣主屹靈祠韻
  author: 權擥
  language: lzh
  text: 祕殿靑山下。陰機白日中。人情聊報祀。神意肯邀功。
korean:
  title: 문경현 주흘영사에 차운하여
  author: 권람
  language: kor
  text: |-
    신비로운 전각 청산 아래 있으니
    명명한 신기는 백일 속일세
    인정이 그저 제사로 갚는 것이지
    귀신 뜻이 어찌 요공하리요
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0670&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Rhyming on the Occasion of the Shrine at Juhul Peak in Mungyeong County
  author: Kwon Ram
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Beneath the emerald hills the sacred temple stands,
    Mystic forces gleam within the light of day.
    Human hearts repay their debts through ritual and prayer—
    Would the gods demand more than what we give?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Juhul Peak (주흘) is a sacred mountain in Mungyeong County, known as a site of spiritual significance in Korean tradition.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem questions the nature of divine reciprocity, suggesting that human sincerity in worship should suffice without the gods seeking additional reward or benefit.
